Eyecube is a sandbox game.

Early version will be rewritten in C++.
Now server and client for terminals (with ncurses) are developed.

Some screenshots are available here: https://picasaweb.google.com/mmaulwurff/Eyecube?authuser=0&feat=directlink

Advices are welcome.


Early Eyecube:

Some keys (',' instead of 'w', 'o' intstead of 's', 'e' intstead of 'd')
are set for Dvorak keyboard.

Compile notes:
(libncurses5-dev should be installed)
gcc -lncurses -pthread

Debug notes:
./Eyecube-*.bin 2>log

Items:
 - Air: passable, transparent. Default block.
 - Grass
 - Stone
 - Chicken: walking chiken. Makes sounds. Burns in a fire.
 - Fire. Burns things as chickens and piles. Dissapears in one hour.
 - Chest. Can contain up to 30 items. Collects items falling on it.
 - Pile. Can contain up to 30 items. Collects items falling on it.
   Dissapears after 24 game hours.
 - Clock: unstackable. If there is a clock in an inventory, exact time is shown instead
   of part of a day.
 - Compass: unstackable. If there is a compass in an inventory, direction is shown.
 - Iron ingot: iron armor (helmet, chestplate, greaves, boots) can be crafted from it.
 - Iron helmet: unstackable. Used as a helmet. Can be crafted from 5 iron ingots.
 - Iron boots: unstackable. Can be crafted from 4 iron ingots.
 - Iron greaves: unstackable. Can be crafted from 7 iron ingots.
 - Iron chestplate: unstackable. Can be crafted from 8 iron ingots.

